The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Mali takes over as acting president

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Cricket South Africa (CSA) president Ray Mali was Thursday appointed as acting president of the International Cricket Council (ICC) following the death of Percy Sonn last month. 

[The Telegraph had reported Thursday that Mali will be appointed acting president till June 2008.] 

Mali will take charge with immediate effect and in doing so will step down as president of CSA, also with immediate effect. 

CSA nominated Mali after the ICC board had asked it to make a nomination in line with a recommendation made by the ICCs Governance Review Committee (GRC) in Cape Town on June 1. 

The Board of Control for Cricket in India had proposed that Mali be appointed acting president of the ICC. 




